lines.text: they've come to destroy the world.
what new friends will the day bring?
what new hope will the night bring?
i saw five hours of sleep.
but your fire makes it all worth while.
i wrote words for you to keep.

paragraphs.text: six figures enter, they've come to destroy the world. they've called together this storm almost every night.
and i awake in another place. a familiar voice with a strangers face speaks, i awake in another place more unheard words.
